<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:11 a.m. 19/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2060" TARGET=_self>So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I am not certain how a matchup will work out as levels increase, but We have a ladder running (and have had some organized arena fights) where high Teen Shaman V. Warriors have fought. From what I have seen, the warrior wooped on the Shaman just in a heads up match, but that surely is not the rule. I am certain that play style, strategy and other factors are involved.

<P>The Shaman did not root...instead went head to head....Also...the rule was the warrior was not allowed to be pre buffed (no buffs by others) but I don't know if that was followed.
<P>Bottom line is that anyone can be competive in PvP (at least that is my belief) if they just think about it and approach each fight based on WHO and WHAT class they are fighting. IE a wizard should not root a spell caster attacking them...instead should just blast faster than they! But a wizzy should root the crap out any warrior type or face CERTAIN doom. A Necro should consider using cancel magic on his rooted pet (if this works life would suck against Necros)....that sort of thing.
<P>The folks that complain about how underpowered their characters are just don't give it a chance. Innoruuk forbid if any of the White Orcs I am fighting now (for 17th) get bows.....
<P>-Gray
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
